Powered by RubiQube Ad Network JOS – Jos has been designated to become a commercial hub of leather processing and production in Nigeria following the commissioning of Jos Hid and skin Entrepreneurship complex by the Nigerian Institute for Science and Technology. Speaking at the commissioning ceremony at the weekend, House of Representatives House Committee Chairman on Science and Technology, Beni Lar, said with the commissioning of Jos extension complex of Hide and skin entrepreneurship centre , Jos will soon out grow Kano in leather production in Nigeria. Hon Lar said the idle Youths in Plateau state would no longer be idling away any more as they have a lot skills acquisition at the centre that would keep them busy.